			<p class="MargenText">
				DECLARATION:<br>
				<br>
				by the Plan Participants to Investors Trust Delaware:<br>
				<br>
				Each Plan Participant jointly and severally:<br>
				<br>
				(1) represents that the information provided by the Plan Participants in this Subscription Agreement is accurate and complete;<br>
				<br>
				(2) acknowledges that a true and complete copy of the 
					<a href="#" class="lnkTahomaGrs9" id="lnkAmended">Amended and Restated Agreement and Declaration of Trust of Investors Trust Delaware</a> 
					(the "Master Agreement"), including a form of 
					<a href="#" class="lnkTahomaGrs9" id="lnkSupplemental">Supplemental Declaration of Trust</a> 
					attached as Exhibit A thereto (the Supplemental Declaration of Trust, substantially in such form, relating to the particular Series of and  with respect to which the Plan Participant is admitted as and becomes a beneficial owner of the Trust, the "Supplemental Agreement")(the Master Agreement, as supplemented by the Supplemental Agreement, is hereinafter referred to as the "Trust Agreement") has been provided to each of them;<br>
				<br>
				(3) desires and hereby applies to participate in the Plan and hereby requests to be admitted as and become a beneficial owner(s) of the Trust with respect to a Series (as defined in the Master Agreement), hereby agrees to be bound by the Master Agreement and the Supplemental Agreement relating to such Series, hereby agrees that the execution of this Subscription Agreement by each Plan Participant also constitutes such Plan Participant's execution of the Master Agreement and the Supplemental Agreement and hereby specifically executes the Master Agreement and the Supplemental Agreement, and hereby constitutes, authorizes, empowers, and appoints each of the Administrator (as defined in the Master Agreement) and any delegatee of the Administrator, acting together or singly, as representative, agent, and attorney-in-fact of each Plan Participant, with full power of substitution (the "Attorney-in-fact"), in the name and on behalf of each Plan Participant, to enter into, execute, and deliver (or take action that is deemed to constitute execution and delivery of) the Master Agreement and such Supplemental Agreement and any and all such other agreements, documents, and instruments as any such Attorney-in-fact deems necessary, appropriate or advisable to effect the intent and purposes of this Subscription Agreement, the Master  Agreement and/or such Supplemental Agreement; and<br> 
				<br>
				(4) directs the Trust to invest funds contributed by the Plan Participants in a Policy issued by the Insurance Company and allocated to such Series.<br>
				<br>
				The Plan Participants hereby represent and acknowledge that each of them has read carefully this Subscription Agreement, the Master Agreement, the Supplemental Agreement, and the form of Policy to be entered into between the Trust and the Insurance Company.<br>
				<br>
				The Plan Participants hereby represent, acknowledge, and agree that the Plan Participants have full responsibility for the selection and choice of Investment Plans.<br>
				<br>
				The Plan Participants hereby represent and acknowledge that each of them has seen and signed the Plan Illustration, attached to this Subscription Agreement.<br>
				<br>
				Each Plan Participant hereby represents and warrants that it is not: (a) a citizen or resident of the United States of America; (b) or a corporation or other entity deemed situated in the United States of America under the tax laws and Regulations (as defined in the Master Agreement) of the United States of America; or (c) physically present in the United States of America for a number of days in a taxable year which would result in it being taxable as a resident alien under the "substantial presence" test of Section 7701(b) of the Code (as defined in the Master Agreement). Each Plan Participant hereby represents, warrants, and agrees that it will deliver notice to the Administrator or its delegatee in accordance to Section 6.2(c) of the Master Agreement if a Tax Termination Event (as defined in the Master Agreement) is expected to occur with respect to such Plan Participant, and that it will deliver notice to the Administrator or its delegatee in accordance with Section 6.2 of the Master Agreement if a Tax Termination Event has occurred with respect to such Plan Participant. Each Plan Participant further understands, acknowledges, and agrees that the occurrence of a Tax Termination Event may result in material adverse tax consequences and that neither the Administrator, the Sponsor, nor the Trustee shall have any personal liability therefor.<br>
				<br>
				The Plan Participants hereby represent, acknowledge, and agree that the Plan Participants have not and will not contribute to the Trust any illegally obtained funds.<br>
				<br>
				The Plan Participants hereby represent, acknowledge, and agree that all funds must be sent directly to the Trust either by check, wire or credit card payment and that any funds given to any intermediary will be at the sole risk of the Plan Participants.<br>
				<br>
				<br>				
				WHEREAS<br>
				<br>
				The Trust has been established under the Delaware Statutory Trust Act, 12 Del. C. ยง 3801 et seq. (the "Act");<br>
				<br>
				In accordance with the terms of the Trust Agreement, the Trust shall purchase on behalf of one or more Series one or more Policies from the Insurance Company, using funds contributed by the Plan Participants;<br>
				<br>
				In accordance with the terms of the Trust Agreement, the Plan Participants shall be admitted as and become the beneficial owners with respect to a Series designated under the Trust Agreement; The Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust, shall direct the Insurance Company to invest the funds contributed by the Plan Participants in the investment funds specified by the Plan Participants in or pursuant to this Subscription Agreement; The Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust, shall administer the Plan in accordance with the terms of the Trust Agreement and this Subscription Agreement and both the selection of the Investment Plans and the Beneficiaries and the mode of distribution of their benefits shall be as set forth by the Plan Participants in this Subscription Agreement.<br>
				<br>
				<br>				
				NOW IT IS HEREBY AGREED AS FOLLOWS<br>
				<br>
				1.	DEFINITIONS<br>
				<br>
				In addition to terms otherwise defined herein, where the context so admits the following expression shall have the following respective meanings:<br>
				<br>
				"Administrator" means, initially, Investors Trust Administration, LLC, acting as the Administrator hereunder and under the Master Agreement, and any Person that becomes its successor as such.<br>
				<br>
				"Beneficiaries" means the Primary Beneficiaries and Contingent Beneficiaries designated in the above section B of this Subscription Agreement as beneficiaries and as applicable  the estate of the Insured designated in Section 6 of this Subscription Agreement as beneficiary.<br>
				<br>
				"Insurance Company" means Investors Trust Assurance SPC on behalf of Investors Trust Segregated Portfolio, or another insurance company (or segregated portfolio thereof) selected by the Sponsor.<br>
				<br>
				"Insured" means the First Plan Participant as the person whose life is insured under each Policy.<br>
				<br>
				"Investment Plans" means the investment funds, specified by the Plan Participants in or pursuant to this Subscription Agreement, in which the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust, shall direct the Insurance Company to invest funds contributed by the Plan Participants.<br>
				<br>
				"Plan" means the arrangement whereby the Trust purchases Policies with monies received from the Plan Participants;<br>
				<br>
				"Policies" means insurance policies, supplemental to a master insurance policy, that insure the life of the Insured and that are purchased from the Insurance Company in accordance with the terms of the Plan.<br>
				<br>
				"Time of Maturity" means the date on which the Investment Plans mature;<br>
				<br>
				"Trust" means the Delaware statutory trust established under the Act and the Master Agreement, currently known as Investors Trust Delaware.<br>
				<br>
				"Trustee" means, initially, CSC Trust Company of Delaware, solely in its capacity as Trustee under the Master Agreement, and any Person that becomes its successor as such.<br>
				<br>
				OTHER INTERPRETATION<br>
				<br>
				(a)	the singular shall include the plural and vice versa;<br>
				<br>
				(b)	the masculine gender shall include the feminine gender and vice versa;<br>
				<br>
				(c)	the neuter gender shall include the masculine and feminine and vice versa;<br>
				<br>
				(d)	persons shall include companies, corporations, organizations, partnerships and other legal entities;<br>
				<br>
				(e)	headings shall not be construed as part of this document;<br>
				<br>
				(f)	this Subscription Agreement shall be construed in tandem with the provisions of the Trust Agreement but to the extent that any provisions hereof are inconsistent therewith, the terms of the Trust Agreement shall prevail;<br>
				<br>
				(g)	capitalized terms used but not otherwise defined in this Subscription Agreement have the meanings assigned thereto in the Trust Agreement.<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				2.	FRAUDULENT DISPOSITIONS<br>
				<br>
				In respect of each transfer of monies or other property to the Trust, the Plan Participants hereby warrant for each transfer that each transfer does now, and will at the time made, comprise property which does not constitute a fraudulent disposition under applicable law, i.e. that each such transfer has not been made at an undervalue and has not been made with an intention to defraud a creditor of the Plan Participant.<br>
				<br>				
				<br>
				3.	THE TRUST INSTRUMENT<br>
				<br>
				A copy of the Master Agreement has been provided to each Plan Participant and each Plan Participant agrees that it shall be subject to and bound by all of the provisions of the Master Agreement, the Supplemental Agreement, and this Subscription Agreement.  Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, each Plan Participant acknowledges and agrees: that funds contributed by a Plan Participant constitute payment for an Interest of a Series to which one or more Policies to be purchased using funds contributed by such Plan Participant are to be allocated; that the making of such contribution constitutes each Plan Participant's agreement to the Master Agreement, the Supplemental Agreement, and this Subscription Agreement and such Plan Participant's agreement to be bound thereby; that the making of such contribution constitutes, authorizes, empowers, and appoints each of the Administrator (as defined in the Master Agreement) and any delegatee of the Administrator, acting together or singly, as representative, agent, and attorney-in-fact of each Plan Participant, with full power of substitution (the "Attorney-in-fact"), in the name and on behalf of each Plan Participant, to enter into, execute, and deliver the Master Agreement and the Supplemental Agreement and any and all such other agreements, documents, and instruments as any such Attorney-in-fact deems necessary, appropriate or advisable to effect the intent and purposes of this Subscription Agreement, the Master Agreement and/or such Supplemental Agreement; that each power of attorney being granted hereby or pursuant hereto by each Plan Participant is being granted for the benefit of the Trust and the holder of such power, is a special power of attorney coupled with an interest, is irrevocable, shall survive and shall not be affected by the subsequent death, disability, or incapacity of the granting Plan Participant and is limited to those matters set forth herein; that the execution and delivery of this Subscription Agreement by a Plan Participant and the acceptance of this Subscription Agreement by the Trust (in accordance with Section 16 below) are the only conditions for a Plan Participant to become a beneficial owner with respect to a Series; and that upon the satisfaction of such conditions each Plan Participant shall be admitted as and become a beneficial owner of the Trust with respect to such Series, and shall become bound by the Master Agreement and such Supplemental Agreement, effective upon the execution and delivery of such Supplemental Agreement by the Trust, the Trustee, and the Administrator or its delegatee as such and as attorney-in-fact of such Plan Participant.<br>
				<br>
				4.	PURCHASE OF THE INVESTMENT PLANS<br>
				<br>
				With funds received from the Plan Participants, the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust, shall purchase one or more Policies and shall continue to pay the premiums due thereon so long as funds contributed by the Plan Participants are available.<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				5.	PAYMENTS TO THE TRUST<br>
				<br>
				The Plan Participants have opted for a method of payment to the Trust, as shown in this Subscription Agreement, and such method may be changed by the Plan Participants, if agreed to by the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust, after written notice requesting a change has been given by the Plan Participants to the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust.<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				6.	THE BENEFICIARIES<br>
				<br>
				The names of those who are to be Beneficiaries of the Policies are (subject to the last sentence of this Section 6) as listed in the above section B of this Subscription Agreement.  At any time, and from time to time, upon receipt by the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust of a written notice signed by all the Plan Participants, Beneficiaries may be deleted or added or the order of their potential benefit may be changed by the Plan Participants.<br>
				<br>
				If there are surviving Primary Beneficiaries at the time of distribution of funds in regard to a Policy received by the Series of the Trust from the Insurance Company upon the death of the Insured under the Policy, payment of such funds shall be made by the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust to the surviving Primary Beneficiaries in proportion to the percentage entitlements of such Primary Beneficiaries as set out in this Subscription Agreement (such that if there is only one surviving Primary Beneficiary such surviving Primary Beneficiary shall receive all such funds).  If there are no surviving Primary Beneficiaries at the time of distribution of funds in regard to a Policy received by the Series of the Trust from the Insurance Company upon the death of the Insured under the Policy, payment of such funds shall be made by the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust to each Contingent Beneficiary in proportion to the percentage entitlements of such Contingent Beneficiary as set out in this Subscription Agreement (such that if there is only one surviving Contingent Beneficiary such surviving Contingent Beneficiary shall receive all such funds). If there are no surviving Primary Beneficiaries or Contingent Beneficiaries at the time of the distribution of funds in regard to a Policy received by the Series of the Trust from the Insurance Company upon the death of the Insured under the Policy, payment of such funds shall be made by the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust to the estate of the Insured.<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				7.	DEFAULT IN CONTRIBUTION PAYMENTS<br>
				<br>
				If the Plan Participants fail to make any contribution due hereunder within 30 days after written notice is given by the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust that a payment is overdue, no further payments will be made in respect of the Policy, and subject to the discretion of the Insurance Company, the Policy will lapse and as permitted by applicable law any funds in regard to the Policy shall be paid to the Plan Participants by the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust at such time as the Trust receives the same from the Insurance Company.<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				8.	INVESTMENT SELECTIONS<br>
				<br>
				To the extent that any Policy enables a choice of investments for a Series, the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust shall instruct that such investments be made in accordance with the directions of the Plan Participants as set forth in this Subscription Agreement.  Changes in investment selection may be made at any time and from time to time by all the Plan Participants as permitted by the Insurance Company, the Investment Plans and the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust.<br>
				<br>
				9.	REVOCATION<br>
				<br>
				The Plan Participants may and in some cases must give written notice of dissolution of a Series to the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust, in which case the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust will surrender to the Insurance Company each Policy allocated to the Series of which the Plan Participants are beneficial owners and upon receipt by the Trust of any funds from the Insurance Company in regard to such a Policy the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust as permitted by law and the Trust Agreement shall distribute such net funds to the Plan Participants.<br> 
				<br>
				The payment, and timing of payments of any such funds to the Plan Participants following a revocation will depend upon the redemption value of each such Policy and the receipt of funds in respect thereof from the Insurance Company.<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				10.	CONFIRMATION OF REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES / INDEMNITY<br>
				<br>
				Each Plan Participant hereby confirms the accuracy of all information and the validity of all representations and warranties provided to the Trust in connection with the Plan and/or the subscription for Investment Plans and for the Policy, howsoever provided, including the terms of this Subscription Agreement and the contents of any personal or medical questionnaire (together "Representations & Warranties").  Each Plan Participant acknowledges that certain of such information will be provided to issuers of the Policy and that any inaccuracy therein may result in the invalidity of such Policy or the investments in the related Investment Plans and the loss of all funds contributed or paid in relation thereto.  Each Plan Participant hereby undertakes to inform the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust of any change in any matter that forms the subject of any of the Representation & Warranties.<br>
				<br>
				Each Plan Participant hereby undertakes to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the Trustee (as such and in its individual capacity) and the Trust against any loss or damage (including, without limitation, attorneys fees) occasioned by any inaccuracy in any Representation & Warranty or failure to advise the Trust of any change in any matter that forms the subject of any of the Representation & Warranties.<br>
				<br>
				Each Plan Participant agrees that the Trustee (as such and in its individual capacity) and the Trust shall be entitled to rely on and to act in accordance with any written instruction purported to be provided by a Plan Participant and each Plan Participant hereby undertakes to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the Trustee (as such and in its individual capacity) and the Trust against any loss or damage (including, without limitation, attorneys fees) occasioned by the Trustee and/or the Trust acting in accordance with any such instruction.<br>
				<br>
				<br>				
				11.	PAYMENT OF BENEFITS<br>
				<br>
				The Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust shall ensure that payments are made to the Beneficiaries in respect of proceeds received from the Insurance Company upon the death of the insured under a Policy, in accordance with the terms hereof, no later than the 10th day of the month following the Trust's receipt thereof.<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				12.	FEES AND EXPENSES<br>
				<br>
				The Trustee and the Administrator each shall charge its fees and expenses as provided in the Trust Agreement.<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				13.	VERIFICATION OF IDENTIFICATION AND SOURCE OF FUNDS<br>
				<br>
				As part of the Trust's responsibility for the prevention of money laundering and in regard to other matters, the Administrator or its delegatee, on behalf of the Trust will require a detailed verification of each Plan Participant's identity and the source of the subscription funds.<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				14.	TRUSTEE'S AND ADMINISTRATOR'S INDEMNITY AND PROTECTIONS<br>
				<br>
				The Trustee, Sponsor, the Administrator, and other Indemnified Parties (each as such and in its individual capacity)) are provided with comprehensive indemnity and other protections in the Trust Agreement as described in the Trust Agreement.<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				15.	GOVERNING LAW<br>
				<br>
				This Agreement is created under and shall be governed by and construed and enforced in accordance with the laws of the State of Delaware (without regard to conflict of laws principles).<br>
				<br>				
				<br>
				16. SUBJECT TO ACCEPTANCE<br>
				<br>
				This Subscription Agreement (which in its entirety consists of pages 1 through 6 hereof) is subject to acceptance by the Trust and will not be an effective agreement unless and until it is accepted by the Trust.  Such acceptance of this Subscription Agreement by the Trust shall be evidenced exclusively by the Trust's execution of the Supplemental Agreement (as defined in the Master Agreement) relating to the Series (as defined in the Master Agreement) of and with respect to which the Plan Participant is to be admitted as and become a beneficial owner of the Trust.<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				17.  DEEMED EXECUTION AND DELIVERY<br>
				<br>
				For all purposes of this Subscription Agreement, the Master Agreement, and the Supplemental Agreement relating to the Series of and with respect to which the Plan Participant is to be admitted as and become a beneficial owner of the Trust, any of the following actions by or on behalf of the Plan Participant shall be deemed to constitute such Person's acceptance, execution and delivery of this Subscription Agreement (including without limitation each Declaration included herein), the Master Agreement, and such Supplemental Agreement: (i) the making of a contribution of funds in payment for an Interest of a Series to which one or more Policies to be purchased using funds contributed by such Plan Participant are to be allocated; or  (ii) Electronic Signature with respect to this Subscription Agreement by or on behalf of such Person.<br>
				<br>
				IN WITNESS WHEREOF THIS SUBSCRIPTION AGREEMENT HAS BEEN EXECUTED AND DELIVERED by each Plan Participant as of the _________day of __________ ,20_____.<br>
				<br>
